        <abstract> 
<p>Thanks AB for his review of <hi rend="italic">Expression</hi> [May 1873, in <hi rend="italic">The senses and the intellect</hi>, 3d ed. (1874), pp. 697–714]. Admits vagueness of some points. Has never grasped AB’s principle of spontaneity. But, as they look at everything so differently, it is not likely that they should agree closely.</p>  
<p>A recent review by T. S. Baynes, [<hi rend="italic">Edinburgh Rev.</hi> 137 (1873): 492–528] is "magnificently contemptuous" toward CD and many others.</p> 
        </abstract>
